"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147151","Ministry of Justice","false","2019-10-07","<p>The responsibilities of a Chief Scientific Advisor are performed by the Director of Analysis in the Ministry of Justice. The Director of Analysis has had three meetings with the Secretary of State between 1 June to 31 August 2019.</p>","Croydon South","Chris Philp",,"2019-10-07T15:21:43.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147151/answer","Biography information for Chris Philp","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147151/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147151/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2019-09-30","Ministry of Justice: Chief Scientific Advisers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many meetings he had with his Department’s Chief Scientific Adviser from 1 June to 31 August 2019.","false","Biography information for Norman Lamb","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb","292143"
