"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147206","Department for Education","false","2019-10-07","<p>Learning about politics is an important part of a broad and balanced education that prepares young people for adult life. All head teachers, however, are required to ensure impartiality and balanced treatment of political issues in schools.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2019-10-07T15:26:37.5Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147206/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147206/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147206/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147206/answer/previousversion/137131","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2019-09-30","Political Parties: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what his Department's policy is on political advertising in schools.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","292164"
