"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147222","Cabinet Office","false","2019-10-03","<p>The Cabinet Office has undertaken to publish information relating to ongoing expenditure on the public information campaign as part of the department’s monthly data transparency releases. The published information will be available on a regular basis on GOV.UK here: (https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/cabinet-office-spend-data)</p><p> </p>","Torbay","Kevin Foster",,"2019-10-03T16:14:42.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147222/answer","Biography information for Kevin Foster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147222/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147222/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2019-09-30","Brexit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster and Minister for the Cabinet Office, pursuant to the Answer of 30 September 2019 to Question 290970 on Brexit, when he plans to publish the costs of the Get Ready for Brexit campaign for (a) August and (b) September 2019.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","292179"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147223","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-08","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-10-08T16:00:17.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147223/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147223/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147223/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-30","General Practitioners: Working Hours","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what procedures are in place to record the number of patients  offered (a) evening and (b) weekend appointments at GP surgeries.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","292364"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147224","Home Office","false","2019-10-08","<p>The Government recognises the damaging impact that violence and abuse toward shop staff can have.</p><p>That is why the National Retail Crime Steering Group brings together Government, the police, retailers and others to help ensure the response to these crimes, and wider related issues, is as robust as it can be. This includes guidance on reporting incidents to the police and the use of Impact Statements for Business which provide victims with a voice in the criminal justice process. The Home Office also provided £60,000 for a targeted communications campaign led by the Association of Convenience Stores to raise awareness.</p><p>In addition, we launched a call for evidence on violence and abuse toward shop staff to help strengthen our understanding of the scale and extent of the issue. The call for evidence has now closed and we are currently analysing responses. We intend to publish the Government’s response in due course.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse",,"2019-10-08T14:20:13.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147224/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147224/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147224/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-09-30","Retail Trade: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps is he taking to strengthen protections for shop workers that face (a) abusive, (b) threatening and (c) violent behaviour.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","292365"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147225","Department for Education","false","2019-10-04","<p>The Department for Education has not spent any money on advertising in schools in relation to the UK leaving the EU in the last 6 months.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is providing its own guidance to the education sectors that it serves, via published information on GOV.UK, support through existing networks and otherwise through the normal conduct of the day-to-day business of the Government.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2019-10-04T12:55:57.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147225/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147225/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147225/answer","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147225/answer/previousversion/137077","Biography information for Nick Gibb","60","Education","Education","2019-09-30","Schools: Advertising","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the cost to the public purse has been on advertising in schools in relation to the UK leaving the EU in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","292166"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147226","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-10-03","<p>The Department has no current plans to make changes to the milk which can be purchased with Healthy Start vouchers, but we are prepared to consider the merits of allowing the purchase of certain plant-based drinks.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill",,"2019-10-03T13:18:17.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147226/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147226/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1147226/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-30","Healthy Start Scheme: Plant Milks","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of extending the Healthy Starts Voucher Scheme to include the purchase of fortified plant milks.","false","Biography information for Paul Farrelly","Newcastle-under-Lyme","Paul Farrelly","292141"
